Gauteng remains in the lead with the highest number of infections standing at 533. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Provincial Government Command Council gave an update on the adherence to the nationwide lockdown. The number of confirmed COVID-19 positive cases has increased to 1187. The Department of Health confirmed the latest figures on Saturday. Gauteng remains in the lead with the highest number of infections standing at 533, while the Northern Cape has the least cases. South Africa has entered day 3 of the 21-days lockdown.